## Conflict & Gap Analysis

> Sources consulted: Confluence — [Lesson Allocation Flow](https://manabie.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/PRDM/pages/1279623170/Lesson+Allocation+Flow) · [Lesson Allocation | Student Allocation Report](https://manabie.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/PRDM/pages/1446477825/Lesson+Allocation+Student+Allocation+Report) · Local test cases in `output/test-cases/lesson-management/student-session/`

### Conflicts with Existing System

| #   | Tag        | Source                                                 | AC               | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         |
| --- | ---------- | ------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1   | [CONFLICT] | Confluence: Lesson Allocation Flow                     | AC 01.1–01.3     | **Dual LA creation paths with no deduplication rule.** The existing system creates LAs exclusively through order flows (New Order Group → Submit, or Enrollment Application → Submit). LT-92532 introduces a new UI-direct path with no order. If staff creates a UI-LA for Course X, then later creates an order for the same Course X, a second order-driven LA may be created — producing duplicate LAs for the same AY + Location + Course. The overlap validation in AC 01.4 guards against date overlaps but may not prevent same-course duplicates if dates differ slightly. |
| 2   | [CONFLICT] | Confluence: Lesson Allocation Flow + AC 02.1 + AC 03.1 | AC 02.1, AC 03.1 | **Three competing Purchased Slot update mechanisms.** (a) Existing system: Purchased_Slot updated by submitting "Update Slot" order (New Order Group → Update → Update Slot). (b) AC 03.1: Purchased_Slot auto-calculated as sum of Contract.Slot, recalculated on contract changes. (c) AC 02.1: Trial LA allows direct UI edit of Purchased Slot to a value > original. Which mechanism wins when all three are simultaneously applicable is undefined.                                                                                                                           |

### Missing in Requirements

| #   | Tag                | Source                                                                                            | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |
| --- | ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1   | [MISSING BEHAVIOR] | Confluence: Lesson Allocation Flow                                                                | **LA deletion by order void/withdrawal/LOA not addressed for UI-created LAs.** The existing system automatically deletes LA when: (a) a new order is voided, (b) withdrawal order submitted with last_attendance_day = start_date, (c) LOA order submitted with last_attendance_day = start_date, (d) enrollment application cancelled. For UI-created LAs (no order association), these triggers presumably do not apply. No AC confirms this isolation or whether a hybrid scenario is possible. |
| 2   | [MISSING BEHAVIOR] | Confluence: Lesson Allocation Flow                                                                | **LA duration auto-update from withdrawal/LOA not addressed.** Existing system: when withdrawal or LOA order is submitted and last_attendance_day > start_date, LA.end_date is set to last_attendance_day. For UI-created LAs, AC 02.1 only allows manual forward-only date edits. The interaction between order-driven duration updates and UI-created LAs is completely absent from the spec.                                                                                                    |
| 3   | [MISSING BEHAVIOR] | Confluence: Student Allocation Report (AC 01.3)                                                   | **`require_allocation` flag value for UI-created LAs is undefined.** The Allocation Dashboard (Confluence page PBT-1049) only displays courses where `require_allocation = TRUE`. The "Add Students" popup in Lesson Management also filters students by LAs where `require_allocation = TRUE` (TC-1261, PX-1517). If UI-created LAs default to `require_allocation = FALSE`, students would be invisible in lesson assignment and the dashboard. LT-92532 makes no mention of this flag.          |
| 4   | [MISSING BEHAVIOR] | `output/test-cases/lesson-management/student-session/student-assignment-lesson-detail.md` TC-1261 | **Lesson "Add Students" popup visibility impacted by `require_allocation` flag.** TC-1261 asserts the popup shows "students that have LA with `require_allocation = TRUE`". If UI-created LAs set this flag to FALSE, students enrolled via LT-92532 flow will not appear in lesson assignment popups, breaking the core lesson scheduling workflow. No AC in LT-92532 covers this downstream effect.                                                                                              |
| 5   | [MISSING BEHAVIOR] | Confluence: Student Allocation Report (AC 01.5)                                                   | **Allocation Dashboard sorting behavior with multiple LAs per course.** Dashboard sorts courses by start_date ASC, end_date ASC, created_at ASC. No AC in LT-92532 addresses how newly created UI LAs appear in and interact with the dashboard, or what happens when multiple LAs exist for the same course with different dates.                                                                                                                                                                 |
| 6   | [MISSING BEHAVIOR] | Confluence: Lesson Allocation Flow                                                                | **Resume LOA creates new LA — potential overlap with UI-created LAs.** Existing system: resuming a LOA order creates a new LA. If a UI-created LA already exists for that course+AY+location, a resume-LOA could create a date-overlapping LA. The overlap validation (AC 01.4) applies only to UI creation; it is unclear whether it also guards against order-driven creation.                                                                                                                   |
| 7   | [MISSING BEHAVIOR] | Confluence: Lesson Allocation Flow                                                                | **Course Master master data prerequisites undocumented.** The LA Flow page shows that Course Offering links to Program Master, Academic Week, and Location Academic Week for session count calculations. LT-92532 AC 01.2 shows a Course selection table that loads after AY + Location are set, but doesn't specify whether Program Master and related master data must exist, or if courses can appear in the list without them.                                                                 |
| 8   | [ROLE GAP]         | AC (all sections)                                                                                 | **Viewer-only roles not addressed.** AC specifies "HQ or CM" as the actor for all actions. No AC defines what Teacher, Back Office admin, or read-only roles see on the Contact → Course tab or the Require LA table. Whether these roles see the "New Lesson Allocation" button, see existing LAs, or are blocked entirely is undefined.                                                                                                                                                          |

### Assumptions Made

- ~~UI-created LAs are assumed to be isolated from the order-driven LA lifecycle.~~ **Confirmed:** UI-created LAs are fully independent of the order flow (void/withdrawal/LOA triggers do not affect them).
- ~~`require_allocation` flag assumed TRUE.~~ **Confirmed:** UI-created LAs set `require_allocation = TRUE`.

