## QASE Coverage Gaps

> Phase 1 (initial import): 375 test cases created in Qase covering AC 01.1–02.2 and AC 03.1/03.2.

### Newly Identified Gaps (from Confluence sources + local test case analysis)

The following scenarios were **not covered** in the initial test case set and require new test cases:

- **`require_allocation` flag** — Verify UI-created LAs set `require_allocation = TRUE`; verify student appears in "Add Students" popup after UI creation
- **Allocation Dashboard appearance** — Verify newly created UI LA appears in the Allocation Dashboard on Contact → Course tab, sorted correctly
- **Allocation Dashboard exclusion** — Verify that if `require_allocation = FALSE` (edge case), the LA does NOT appear in the dashboard
- **Order-driven LA vs UI-created LA coexistence** — Verify no duplicate LA is created when an order is submitted for a course that already has a UI-created LA
- **Void order isolation** — Verify voiding a (subsequent) order does NOT delete a UI-created LA that has no order association
- **Withdrawal order isolation** — Verify submitting a withdrawal order does not alter dates or status of UI-created LAs for the same student/course
- **LOA order isolation** — Verify LOA submission does not alter UI-created LAs
- **Lesson "Add Students" popup** — End-to-end: create LA via UI → open lesson → click Add Students → verify student appears with correct course filter
- **Dashboard sort order** — Create 3 LAs for same student with different start dates; verify they appear in correct sort order in the Allocation Dashboard
